<!-- ══════ SERVICE DETAIL ══════ -->
<section id="flooring-details" class="svc-detail" style="scroll-margin-top:var(--nav-h);">
  <div class="svc-detail-grid">
    <div>
      <div class="eyebrow"><span class="eyebrow-line"></span><span class="eyebrow-text">What We Install</span></div>
      <h2 class="section-title">EVERY FLOOR.<br>EVERY FINISH.</h2>
      <div class="gold-rule"></div>
      <p class="svc-detail-body">Whether you are renovating your Halifax home, finishing a new build in Bedford, or updating a rental property in Dartmouth, choosing the right flooring matters. At ETRA Pro Services, we install a wide range of flooring materials and take the time to help you understand which option works best for your space, lifestyle, and budget.</p>
      <p class="svc-detail-body">We have installed flooring in homes and commercial spaces across the Halifax Regional Municipality -- from downtown condos to family homes in Sackville and Cole Harbour. Every project gets the same attention to detail: careful measurement, proper subfloor preparation, and a clean, professional finish that lasts.</p>
      <p class="svc-detail-body">Our team handles everything from a single room to entire floor plans. If your subfloor needs work before the new flooring goes down, we take care of that too -- no need to hire a separate contractor.</p>

      <div class="areas-callout">
        <div class="areas-callout-title">Serving All of HRM</div>
        <p class="areas-callout-body">We install flooring throughout <strong>Halifax</strong>, <strong>Dartmouth</strong>, <strong>Bedford</strong>, <strong>Sackville</strong>, <strong>Cole Harbour</strong>, <strong>Fall River</strong>, <strong>Eastern Passage</strong>, <strong>Timberlea</strong>, <strong>Hammonds Plains</strong>, <strong>Tantallon</strong>, <strong>Waverley</strong>, <strong>Enfield</strong>, <strong>Elmsdale</strong>, <strong>Porters Lake</strong>, and surrounding areas. Not sure if we cover your location? Just ask -- we will let you know right away.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div>
      <div class="svc-types-title">FLOORING TYPES WE INSTALL</div>
      <div class="svc-type-card">
        <div class="svc-type-item">
          <span class="svc-type-icon">◈</span>
          <div>
            <div class="svc-type-name">Vinyl Plank Flooring</div>
            <div class="svc-type-desc">Durable, waterproof, and available in a wide range of wood-look finishes. Vinyl plank is one of the most popular choices for Halifax homeowners -- it handles moisture well and stands up to heavy foot traffic, making it ideal for kitchens, bathrooms, basements, and entryways.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="svc-type-item">
          <span class="svc-type-icon">◈</span>
          <div>
            <div class="svc-type-name">Luxury Vinyl Plank (LVP)</div>
            <div class="svc-type-desc">A step up in thickness, texture, and realism. LVP offers a premium look and feel with enhanced durability, and it is a smart choice for high-traffic areas in both homes and commercial spaces. Click-lock or glue-down -- we do both.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="svc-type-item">
          <span class="svc-type-icon">◈</span>
          <div>
            <div class="svc-type-name">Hardwood Flooring</div>
            <div class="svc-type-desc">Timeless beauty and long-term value. We install solid hardwood and engineered hardwood with precision fitting, proper expansion gaps, and clean transitions. A natural choice for living rooms, dining areas, and bedrooms.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="svc-type-item">
          <span class="svc-type-icon">◈</span>
          <div>
            <div class="svc-type-name">Tile Flooring</div>
            <div class="svc-type-desc">Porcelain, ceramic, and natural stone tile installation. Perfect for bathrooms, kitchens, mudrooms, and commercial entrances. We ensure level surfaces, consistent grout lines, and sealed finishes that last.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="svc-type-item">
          <span class="svc-type-icon">◈</span>
          <div>
            <div class="svc-type-name">Laminate Flooring</div>
            <div class="svc-type-desc">An affordable alternative that still delivers a clean, modern look. Laminate installs quickly and works well for bedrooms, offices, and rental units where budget and durability need to balance.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══════ SUBFLOOR REPAIR ══════ -->
<section class="subfloor-section">
  <div class="subfloor-grid">
    <div>
      <div class="eyebrow"><span class="eyebrow-line"></span><span class="eyebrow-text">Preparation Matters</span></div>
      <h2 class="section-title">SUBFLOOR<br>REPAIR &<br>PREP.</h2>
      <div class="gold-rule"></div>
      <p class="svc-detail-body">A great floor starts with what is underneath it. Many flooring problems -- squeaks, uneven surfaces, warping, and premature wear -- come down to a subfloor that was not properly prepared before installation. We address these issues before your new flooring goes down, not after.</p>
      <p class="svc-detail-body">Whether it is an older home in Halifax's South End that needs leveling compound, or a new construction project in Fall River that needs moisture testing, our team handles the preparation work that keeps your floors performing for years to come.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="svc-types-title">WHAT WE HANDLE</div>
      <div class="subfloor-features">
        <div class="subfloor-feat">Subfloor leveling and smoothing</div>
        <div class="subfloor-feat">Damaged subfloor replacement</div>
        <div class="subfloor-feat">Moisture testing and vapor barriers</div>
        <div class="subfloor-feat">Old flooring and adhesive removal</div>
        <div class="subfloor-feat">Plywood and OSB subfloor repair</div>
        <div class="subfloor-feat">Transition strips and trim installation</div>
        <div class="subfloor-feat">Underlayment selection and installation</div>
        <div class="subfloor-feat">Expansion gap planning for seasonal movement</div>
      </div>

      <div class="areas-callout">
        <div class="areas-callout-title">No Surprises</div>
        <p class="areas-callout-body">If we find subfloor issues during your project, we discuss the problem and the solution with you before any extra work begins. Our quotes are honest and transparent -- that is how we do business across every project in HRM.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

